From Not a Boomer Subject Re F O CUS HEALTH The Big Secret In article writes IT IS A MATTER OF LOGIC that government run systems are inefficient and the fact that the highly bureaucratized private sector system in the US is vastly more inefficient is therefore Proof that the entire private sector is vastly more inefficient It is for example of no relevance that Blue Cross of Massachusetts employs people more than are employed in all of Canada's health programs which insure times as many people Blue Cross is the government health insurance Ads for Z magazine deleted to Save the Earth Brett There's nothing so passionate as a vested interest disguised as an intellectual Sean O'Casey in The White Plague by Frank